@page "/ControlSamples/CalendarExtender"
@rendermode InteractiveServer
@using BlazorAjaxToolkitComponents
@using BlazorAjaxToolkitComponents.Enums

<PageTitle>CalendarExtender Component Samples</PageTitle>

<h2>CalendarExtender Component</h2>

<p>The <code>CalendarExtender</code> attaches a popup calendar date picker to a target textbox. When the user clicks or focuses the textbox, a calendar appears for date selection. This emulates the Ajax Control Toolkit <code>CalendarExtender</code>.</p>

<div class="alert alert-info">
    <strong>Note:</strong> Extender components render <strong>no HTML</strong> themselves — they attach JavaScript behavior to an existing target element identified by <code>TargetControlID</code>. This page requires <code>InteractiveServer</code> render mode for JS interop.
</div>

<hr />

<h3>1. Basic Date Picker</h3>
<p>Attach a calendar popup to a textbox with the default <code>MM/dd/yyyy</code> format.</p>

<div data-audit-control="CalendarExtender-1">
    <label for="txtBasicDate">Select a date:</label>
    <input type="text" id="txtBasicDate" class="form-control" style="max-width: 250px;" placeholder="Click to pick a date" />
    <CalendarExtender TargetControlID="txtBasicDate" Format="MM/dd/yyyy" />
</div>

<pre><code>&lt;input type="text" id="txtBasicDate" /&gt;
&lt;CalendarExtender TargetControlID="txtBasicDate" Format="MM/dd/yyyy" /&gt;</code></pre>

<hr />

<h3>2. Date Range Constraints</h3>
<p>Use <code>StartDate</code> and <code>EndDate</code> to restrict selectable dates. Dates outside the range are disabled.</p>

<div data-audit-control="CalendarExtender-2">
    <label for="txtRangeDate">Pick a date (this month only):</label>
    <input type="text" id="txtRangeDate" class="form-control" style="max-width: 250px;" placeholder="Restricted range" />
    <CalendarExtender TargetControlID="txtRangeDate"
                      Format="MM/dd/yyyy"
                      StartDate="@startOfMonth"
                      EndDate="@endOfMonth" />
    <small class="text-muted">Range: @startOfMonth.ToString("MM/dd/yyyy") to @endOfMonth.ToString("MM/dd/yyyy")</small>
</div>

<pre><code>&lt;input type="text" id="txtRangeDate" /&gt;
&lt;CalendarExtender TargetControlID="txtRangeDate"
                  Format="MM/dd/yyyy"
                  StartDate="@@startOfMonth"
                  EndDate="@@endOfMonth" /&gt;</code></pre>

<hr />

<h3>3. Different Date Formats</h3>
<p>The <code>Format</code> property accepts .NET date format strings.</p>

<div data-audit-control="CalendarExtender-3">
    <div class="row g-3">
        <div class="col-auto">
            <label for="txtShortDate">Short (d):</label>
            <input type="text" id="txtShortDate" class="form-control" style="width: 200px;" />
            <CalendarExtender TargetControlID="txtShortDate" Format="d" />
        </div>
        <div class="col-auto">
            <label for="txtLongDate">yyyy-MM-dd:</label>
            <input type="text" id="txtLongDate" class="form-control" style="width: 200px;" />
            <CalendarExtender TargetControlID="txtLongDate" Format="yyyy-MM-dd" />
        </div>
        <div class="col-auto">
            <label for="txtEuroDate">dd/MM/yyyy:</label>
            <input type="text" id="txtEuroDate" class="form-control" style="width: 200px;" />
            <CalendarExtender TargetControlID="txtEuroDate" Format="dd/MM/yyyy" />
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<pre><code>&lt;input type="text" id="txtShortDate" /&gt;
&lt;CalendarExtender TargetControlID="txtShortDate" Format="d" /&gt;

&lt;input type="text" id="txtLongDate" /&gt;
&lt;CalendarExtender TargetControlID="txtLongDate" Format="yyyy-MM-dd" /&gt;</code></pre>

<hr />

<h3>4. PopupPosition Options</h3>
<p>Control where the calendar appears relative to the textbox using <code>PopupPosition</code>.</p>

<div data-audit-control="CalendarExtender-4">
    <div class="row g-3">
        <div class="col-auto">
            <label for="txtBottomLeft">BottomLeft:</label>
            <input type="text" id="txtBottomLeft" class="form-control" style="width: 180px;" />
            <CalendarExtender TargetControlID="txtBottomLeft" Format="MM/dd/yyyy"
                              PopupPosition="CalendarPosition.BottomLeft" />
        </div>
        <div class="col-auto">
            <label for="txtBottomRight">BottomRight:</label>
            <input type="text" id="txtBottomRight" class="form-control" style="width: 180px;" />
            <CalendarExtender TargetControlID="txtBottomRight" Format="MM/dd/yyyy"
                              PopupPosition="CalendarPosition.BottomRight" />
        </div>
        <div class="col-auto">
            <label for="txtTopLeft">TopLeft:</label>
            <input type="text" id="txtTopLeft" class="form-control" style="width: 180px;" />
            <CalendarExtender TargetControlID="txtTopLeft" Format="MM/dd/yyyy"
                              PopupPosition="CalendarPosition.TopLeft" />
        </div>
        <div class="col-auto">
            <label for="txtRight">Right:</label>
            <input type="text" id="txtRight" class="form-control" style="width: 180px;" />
            <CalendarExtender TargetControlID="txtRight" Format="MM/dd/yyyy"
                              PopupPosition="CalendarPosition.Right" />
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<pre><code>&lt;input type="text" id="txtBottomLeft" /&gt;
&lt;CalendarExtender TargetControlID="txtBottomLeft"
                  PopupPosition="CalendarPosition.BottomLeft" /&gt;

&lt;input type="text" id="txtRight" /&gt;
&lt;CalendarExtender TargetControlID="txtRight"
                  PopupPosition="CalendarPosition.Right" /&gt;</code></pre>

<hr />

<h3>Migration Guide: Ajax Control Toolkit to Blazor</h3>

<h4>Ajax Control Toolkit (Before)</h4>
<pre><code class="language-aspx">&lt;asp:ScriptManager ID="ScriptManager1" runat="server" /&gt;
&lt;asp:TextBox ID="txtDate" runat="server" /&gt;
&lt;ajaxToolkit:CalendarExtender ID="CalendarExtender1" runat="server"
    TargetControlID="txtDate"
    Format="MM/dd/yyyy"
    PopupPosition="BottomLeft" /&gt;</code></pre>

<h4>Blazor with BWFC (After)</h4>
<pre><code>&lt;input type="text" id="txtDate" /&gt;
&lt;CalendarExtender TargetControlID="txtDate"
                  Format="MM/dd/yyyy"
                  PopupPosition="CalendarPosition.BottomLeft" /&gt;</code></pre>

<h4>Migration Steps</h4>
<ol>
    <li>Remove <code>asp:ScriptManager</code></li>
    <li>Replace <code>&lt;asp:TextBox&gt;</code> with <code>&lt;input type="text"&gt;</code> keeping the same <code>id</code></li>
    <li>Replace <code>&lt;ajaxToolkit:CalendarExtender&gt;</code> with <code>&lt;CalendarExtender&gt;</code></li>
    <li>Keep <code>TargetControlID</code> and <code>Format</code> values unchanged</li>
    <li>Prefix enum values with type name: <code>PopupPosition="CalendarPosition.BottomLeft"</code></li>
    <li>Ensure the page uses <code>@@rendermode InteractiveServer</code></li>
</ol>

@code {
    private DateTime startOfMonth = new DateTime(DateTime.Today.Year, DateTime.Today.Month, 1);
    private DateTime endOfMonth = new DateTime(DateTime.Today.Year, DateTime.Today.Month, DateTime.DaysInMonth(DateTime.Today.Year, DateTime.Today.Month));
}
